Definitions

  • Pre-treatment characteristics are defined according to the entered treatment start date.
  • The closest, valid result prior to treatment starting is used for the purpose of this table.
  • Data recorded after treatment has started will not be reflected in this table.
  • Since age is only entered once into the EMR, it has been recalculated to reflect age at treatment start.
  • The current calendar month, calendar year and the full programme data is presented here.

Definition

  • Treatment episode outcomes are presented meaning patients treated multiple times are counted more than once.

  • The treatment cohort is defined as episodes starting greater than 15 months (for DS-TB) or 30 months (for DR-TB) prior to reporting such that all outcomes should be available.

  • Loss to follow-up (LTFU) is defined by the user and is not automatically calculated.
